Revolutionizing the Home Loan Experience



Buying a home is a really big deal. We get that. Whether you’re in search of your first home – or you’ve been down this path before – you’ll have questions and concerns. You may even hit some dead ends and bumps in the road.

But that’s okay. We’re well-equipped to go through the journey with you. For more than 28 years, we’ve been helping customers like you navigate the home-buying and refinancing processes.

We’ve been making the American dream of homeownership come true for families throughout the United States since Glenn Stearns founded our company in 1989. 

Today, Stearns Lending has revolutionized home financing to make the process faster, simpler and more secure. Harnessing the power of technology and the passion of our people, we’ll give you a personalized mortgage experience.





Our Culture














Our Mission Statement

When we say, “I Can Help You!” we are making a commitment to helping people reach their goals and achieve their dreams.  That’s true in every interaction we have with customers and with each other. 
 
“I Can Help You!” means we view colleagues, employees, customers and clients as individuals – not as transactions. It places the focus on them, emphasizing a willingness to give as much as receive. 
 
We make a commitment to get the job done correctly and on time – with integrity, responsibility and accountability. We will do what we said we will do, and deliver on promises made.
          
      









Lending Hands 

The "I Can Help You!" culture at Stearns is about assisting others, including giving back and making a difference in the communities where we live and work. In 2016, we partnered with HomeAid America to provide toiletry CareKits for the homeless. Our team members went all out and collected more than 30,000 Care Kit items during the month of November.

Our goal was to provide 2,300 Care Kits, and we succeeded in producing nearly double that number. In addition, hundreds of Stearns employees donated items and volunteered their time. It was a powerful demonstration that the "I can help you" culture at Stearns includes making a positive difference in the lives of others.
    
     










